&lt;p&gt;&quot;Because read repair didn&apos;t actually wait around for repair writes to ack, there was a non-zero chance of multiple concurrent read requests to a needing-repair key triggering multiple repair writes?&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13479316" author="jbellis" created="Thu, 18 Oct 2012 20:10:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That, and &quot;it was possible for a quorum read to return an old value, even after a quorum read had returned a newer value &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;but the newer value had not yet been sent to the other replicas&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
